/sagityo/about/about05.html|title=色短冊 - 勝山左義長について|accessdate=2020-10-21|publisher=勝山市}}</ref> ; Dondo-Yaki On the second night, sacred decorations are burned at Benten Riverbank in a fire ceremony. This ritual is connected to Shinto purification practices.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.city.katsuyama.fukui.jp/kankou/sagityo/about/about09.html|title=どんど焼き・後燃やし - 勝山左義長について|accessdate=2020-10-21|publisher=勝山市}}</ref> == See Also == * {{ill|Katsuyama Castle Museum|ja|勝山城博物館}} - Features exhibits on Sagicho, including drumming experiences. * {{ill|Makoto Shiina|ja|椎名誠}} - Praised the festival in his work, becoming a "Katsuyama Sagicho Ambassador" in {{ill|2010|ja|平成22nd year }}. * {{ill|Echitetsu Monogatari|ja|えちてつ物語〜わたし、故郷に帰ってきました。}} - Features Sagicho drum scenes.
